                <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-12 ">
                    <div class="accordion" id="accordionExample" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="3000">

                        <div class="accordion-item mb-3">
                            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">When
                                    should I start marketing my book?
                                </button>
                            </h2>
                            <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne"
                                data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                                <div class="accordion-body">
                                    <p>Start three to four months before your release date. That gives you time to build
                                        early reviews, set up ads, and create buzz. I have seen authors start two weeks
                                        before launch and scramble to get any traction. Give yourself room. A slow build
                                        beats a frantic last-minute push every time.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="accordion-item mb-3">
                            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">Do I
                                    need a big budget to market my book?</button>
                            </h2>
                            <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo"
                                data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                                <div class="accordion-body">
                                    <p>No. I have run successful campaigns on small budgets. The key is focus. You do not
                                        need to be everywhere. You need to be in the right places. We help you prioritize
                                        what actually works for your genre. Some authors spend thousands on ads that go
                                        nowhere. Smart targeting beats big spending.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="accordion-item mb-3">
                            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
                                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false"
                                    aria-controls="collapseThree">What if my book has been out for a while?</button>
                            </h2>
                            <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree"
                                data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                                <div class="accordion-body">
                                    <p>That is fine. Books do not expire. I have run campaigns for books published years
                                        ago. The approach changes a bit. We look for fresh angles, seasonal hooks, or new
                                        audiences. Sometimes a book just needs a second chance with the right readers. We
                                        can breathe new life into a title that people missed the first time.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="accordion-item mb-3">
                            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree1">
                                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseThree1" aria-expanded="false"
                                    aria-controls="collapseThree1">How do you measure marketing success?</button>
                            </h2>
                            <div id="collapseThree1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree1"
                                data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                                <div class="accordion-body">
                                    <p>We look at real outcomes. Did your book climb in category rankings? Did your email
                                        list grow? Did you get reviews from actual readers? I do not care about vanity
                                        metrics like impressions. I care about whether readers are buying your book and
                                        telling their friends about it. That is success.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="accordion-item mb-3">
                            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree2">
                                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseThree2" aria-expanded="false"
                                    aria-controls="collapseThree2"> Can I do marketing myself without hiring an
                                    agency?</button>
                            </h2>
                            <div id="collapseThree2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree2"
                                data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                                <div class="accordion-body">
                                    <p>You can. Many authors do. But it takes time, consistency, and a willingness to learn.
                                        If you have a full-time job or you would rather spend your energy writing, hiring
                                        help makes sense. We handle the heavy lifting so you can focus on what you do best.
                                        You stay involved. We handle the execution.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="accordion-item mb-3">
                            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree3">
                                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseThree3" aria-expanded="false"
                                    aria-controls="collapseThree3">What marketing channels work best for authors?</button>
                            </h2>
                            <div id="collapseThree3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree3"
                                data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                                <div class="accordion-body">
                                    <p>It depends on your genre. Romance authors thrive on Facebook ads and TikTok. Business
                                        authors do better with LinkedIn and email newsletters. Mystery writers often find
                                        success with BookBub and reader groups. We look at your genre and your audience and
                                        build a channel mix that makes sense. No one-size-fits-all approach.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>


